"""Generated SAP ECC business reference (Ivy Data Company dataset).

Source: SAP_ECC_Business_Glossary.xlsx (557 fields) + _DATASET_CATALOG.csv
(table->module) + verified actual column headers. The disambiguation block
is hand-authored from findings verified against the real files.

Exposes SAP_DISAMBIGUATION, GLOSSARY_BY_MODULE, TABLE_MODULE,
build_sap_glossary(table_names).
"""
from __future__ import annotations

SAP_DISAMBIGUATION = 'CRITICAL FIELD DISAMBIGUATION (verified against the actual files — read before picking a table):\n- "value type" / "plan vs actual" → WRTTP (01=plan, 04=actual), found in COSP, COSS, COEP, COBK.\n  Group cost by WRTTP. Do NOT use VRGAR — VRGAR is the COPA Record Type (in KEKO/KEPH/CKIS/CKMLHD), not a value type.\n- "planned cost" / "actual cost" amounts → period value columns WKG001..WKG0nn in COSP/COSS (totals),\n  or WOGBTR/WTGBTR in COEP (line items). ERLOS = Revenue and VVAUF/VVUMS/VVCOG = COPA value fields\n  (order intake / sales / COGS) — these are NOT general "cost"; never sum ERLOS for a cost question.\n- KEPH and CKMLPR (and KEKO, CKIS, CKMLHD) are COPA/costing twins that share ERLOS/VVAUF/VVUMS/VVCOG/VRGAR.\n  They answer profitability/COPA questions, NOT "plan vs actual cost by value type" — that is COSP/COSS/COEP.\n- TCURR in THIS dataset holds TREASURY deal data (RFHA, DEAL_DATE, BZBETR, PARTNER, PRODUCT_TYPE), NOT\n  currency exchange rates. Use it as a treasury table; do not treat it as an FX-rate lookup.\n- When two shortlisted tables share an identical column set (schema twins), pick the one whose business\n  purpose (per the glossary below) matches the question; if still ambiguous, state which you chose and why.'

